!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

horizontal /ˌhɒrɪˈzɒntəl/

1. ADJ Something that is horizontal is flat and level with the ground, rather than at an angle to it. 水平的; 横的 

例： The board consists of vertical and horizontal lines. 牌子是由纵向和横向的线条构成的。 

2. N-SING Horizontal is also a noun. 水平线; 水平面 

例： Do not raise your left arm above the horizontal. 不要把你的左臂举过水平位置。 

3. horizontally ADV 水平地 

例： The wind was cold and drove the snow at him almost horizontally. 风很冷，裹着雪几乎是横着向他扑来。

</div>

